cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object discovery and detector adaptation from video sequences. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper uses video datasets from autonomous driving and mobile robotics scenarios. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a novel approach for unsupervised object discovery by appearance-based clustering. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with object mining and detector adaptation, which are important tasks in AI. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also relevant as the paper deals with video datasets and object discovery from multimedia sources.
